<A>__{on karen as she comes to. her wounds have been bandaged. she rises, a little shaky, takes in her surroundings she's in a spartan room, like a monk's cell. on the wall is a collection of knives and daggers. some of them wooden, their hilts inscribed with bizarre looking runes. in the center of these weapons rests blade's sword, hanging like a cross in a chapel, dominating all else. karen touches it. then her eyes drop to a silver locket which dangles from the hilt by a tarnished chain. she reaches for it, opens it the locket features a photo, old and faded. it's the black woman we saw in the prologue, vanessa, standing in the sunshine. karen moves towards the door, cautious }
